page: Bachelor of Medicine, Bachelor of Surgery
message: The BS, MD program and the MVVS both are primary medical qualifications and the equivalent of one another in that respect. The point is that a BS,MD, although a graduate level course, is achieved in the same time as those enrolled in traditional 6 year MBBS programs (undergraduate) with the end result being two primary medical qualifications that are equivalent in attainment time and scope of practice.

page: Bachelor of Medicine, Bachelor of Surgery
message: /* United States */  Someone mis stated that an MBBS was equivalent to an MD in many institutions in the US and that is not the truth not even in the early choice college medical programs spoken about because an undergraduate degree is still needed; although it is shortened to 6 cumulative years instead of 8. The other additions were because the section was was lacking for comparison so people could make a more informed choice to where they would want to study or practice.
